      <scopecontent id="aspace_e68e91fc67bba16f2a40f6021c41d65d">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The Andrew Keogh Papers consist largely of memos, outlines, notes, bibliographies, newspaper clippings and other materials pertaining to the courses in bibliography that Keogh taught at Yale from 1924 to 1938. The papers are arranged alphabetically by subject, the titles in quotations being Keogh's original folder titles.</p>
         <p>A folder of correspondence, for the most part personal letters to Keogh and coinciding with his early years at the Yale Library, follows the bibliographical material. Other letters, some to Keogh, some copies of letters from him, are filed in the subject folders under the topic which they specifically concern.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <bioghist id="aspace_d838ca02eb5ebbb544cd1a1f56d55610">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Andrew Keogh: reference librarian, Newcastle (Eng.) Public Libraries, 1892-1898; librarian of Linonia and Brothers Library at Yale University, 1899-1900; Yale University reference librarian, 1900-1916; Yale Librarian, 1916-1938; librarian emeritus, 1938-1953; lecturer and then professor of bibliography, 1902-1938; professor emeritus, 1938-1953.</p>  
      </bioghist>
